result.name: Sushi Tokami

reviews.text: The sushi was delicious - obviously very fresh and a good cut for all the different fish we sampled. The service was quick and friendly. We left fully satisfied and would come back if we lived locally.

Food was alright and reasonably priced for a Michelin starred sushiya. Atmosphere and communication with chef was subpar, quite often the sushi chef here doesn't cut the fish and neta by himself, resulting in an incoherent dining experience. Maguro tossaki was the highlight😚
the BEST SUSHI in hong kong! and the chef is the funniest too hahaha

Sushi Tokami is an offshoot of the very popular sushi-ya in Tokyo (Chef Sato-san of Hakkoku and Tokami fame).

As many reviewers have already mentioned, the owners of Tokami are also owners of a very reputable Tuna supplier in Tokyo, hence the consistently high quality of the fish (neta).

This is a great place for a special occasion (it’s rather pricey!), and definitely one of the best sushi-yas in Hong Kong.

We had about 5 otsumamis and 12 nigiris before dessert and fruits. Couple of interesting dishes that were not common (baby eel, and the tuna tossaki roll which was pretty bloody awesome). The shari is warm with a slight tang and was the perfect bed for the neta.

Chef spoke a little English and Cantonese and was engaged with all customers throughout dinner service, which is pretty impressive considering there’re 10 seats compared to most omakase counters with only 6-8 seats.

Good for: special date night, when you’re feeling bourgeoisie, when you don’t know how else to spend your money.

Michelin star resturant.
Amazing food. Friendly staff.
Def gona come again !

reviews.text: Ocean Centre is a sprawling shopping centre that's located right on the harbour of Tsim Sha Tsui. There's a lot of variety in here but most of the goods are from the higher end brands and designers. They always have the latest and the shopping experience here is nice. There's also a good number of restaurants. The toilets here are very clean.
Nice place highly recommended
Quite some nice shops and restaurants with a small outdoor area at the very end and little later on the top deck.
Amazing shopping centre absolutely huge!!!!
Refused entry at 2pm!!! (Lunchtime hours listed as 1pm to 3pm) An absolute disgrace. Do they discriminate against Western customers?? Avoid this restaurant at all cost!!!
